summary: Hey Sunny! What's your favorite theory/speculation for GoT S8?
question: Hey Sunny! What's your favorite theory/speculation for GoT S8?
answer:
Oooh, good question.  I’m putting this under the cut for potential spoilers.

My favorite GoT theory/speculation is Sansa being kidnapped and taken to King’s Landing.  When I first heard of it, my reaction was meh.  But after reading metas and thinking about it, I’d be excited to see that unfold on screen.

As it has been pointed out before (I think by you, in fact), it would resolve the Cersei/Sansa confrontation that has been hinted at for a few seasons now. I’m sure Cersei is especially incensed after Sansa didn’t go to KL in s7.

What else do I want with this?

  • for Jon to go *kill Bill sirens* ape shit when he finds out 
  • for Sansa to be able to save herself, BUT for Jon to try and save her anyways 
    • I’d like there to be a twist on Sansa being the typical damsel in distress and put what she learned from both Cersei and LF to good use.  
    • Regardless, it would be nice for Sansa to be assured that she does have a hero in Jon, and that he could keep his promise in protecting her.
  • And since I’m a sucker for all things Tangled, I’d love for future gifsets of Jon and Sansa to be paralleled (yet again) with Eugene and Rapunzel when Eugene tries to save Rapunzel from Mother Gothel (Cersei)

Special shout-out to the amazing fic and no net ensnares me by @athimbleful. I haven’t finished it yet, but it’s checking off everything I’m wanting to see in the show, so it’s a definite fic rec.

caption:
As we can see with Jeyne Poole, Northerners actually can coil their braids in a style similar to D/ny’s. But that’s not the hairstyle Sansa has at all and seeing her compared to Jeyne only makes that so much more clear.

Sansa’s s8 hair seems more inspired by her mother’s hairstyle at the Red Wedding. Yes, there are differences but the silhouettes are a lot more similar.

summary: Also I hate the Aegon and his sisters comparisons with Jon/Sansa/Arya. I don't understand why Starks fans like those comparisons...
question: Also I hate the Aegon and his sisters comparisons with Jon/Sansa/Arya. I don't understand why Starks fans like those comparisons knowing what the did and the relationship of the Starks and Targs. I know it started with the books but it's just irritating, unnecessary, and not interesting in my opinion. You can examine the relationship of the latter trio w/o relating them to the former. It feels like everything must relate to the Targs even when they're not supposed to be the main family.
answer:
I hate Aegon and Rhaenys, Visenya is pretty cool despite also being a major mass murdering asshole but she owned up to that shit at least. I never liked the whole Aegon and his sisters thing, I was squinting when I saw Arya and Dany stans doing it. Why would you want your favourite characters emulating those three? They are bad people and two of them screwed over the third one. Aegon was supposed to marry Visenya but he married Rhaenys too and decided he only wanted to have kids with Rhaenys (meaning she’ll be the mother of his dynasty, something he was denying Visenya). He treated his child with Rhaenys better than his child with Visenya, he was cold towards Visenya after Rhaenys died and despite his decisions as king not lasting long after he died, he is remembered better than his sisters.

Anyway, let’s stop comparing the Starks to these people please.

summary: I thought the wig for Sophie looked much improved from last season. At least when Sansa triumphs at the end, a questionable wig...
question: I thought the wig for Sophie looked much improved from last season. At least when Sansa triumphs at the end, a questionable wig won't be able to distract from it. It's slightly shallow, I know, but I can't help it since she's had nothing but great hairstyles the seasons before. Anyway the teaser confirmed what I always knew which was that Sansa will have to spend the last season saving Jon from his fuck-ups.
answer:
To be honest with you unless a wig is really fucked up, I don’t notice. I do think her hair is nicer this season and her makeup is well done. I was hoping for a new outfit. I loved Sansa’s dresses in the early seasons but she’s been in black and a cloak for two seasons now. Give me something new.

I said this in the other post (but everyone focused on anon’s insults) but I really want Sansa have a separate storyline. Jon has the Night King, Daenerys and his parents to deal with. Bran has the Night King to deal with. Cersei is trying to keep the throne. Dany wants to win the throne. I want Sansa to have her own conflicts and triumphs. I want to see her prepare the North and Winterfell, I want her politicking with and against Dany, I want her talking about her mother (why is everyone ignoring her). I don’t have a problem with Sansa protecting her siblings but I’m scared d&d will make her focus solely on Jon’s safety and wellbeing. C’mon all those seasons of learning and adapting for just that?

summary: Interestingly enough, this new trailer contains quotes from Catelyn, Lyanna and Ned. And then we have another trio: Sansa, Arya...
body:
Interestingly enough, this new trailer contains quotes from Catelyn, Lyanna and Ned. And then we have another trio: Sansa, Arya and Jon.

The parallel here is evident.

Arya was always compared to Lyanna. Not only does she very much look like her, according to many people, including her own father; but she is also a fighter like Lyanna. Both are wild, both carry weapons. They are the wild wolves, the unpredictable, the fiery ones. Both are gamechangers. 

Sansa is obviously Catelyn. They look like each other, and Sansa’s clothes and hair increasingly mirror Catelyn’s over the seasons. Both are Ladies of Winterfell and assist the Lord in his duties. Just like her mother, Sansa is a lady, a strong woman although she doesn’t fight with weapons. Both fight to protect their family. Both are the quiet, discrete ones who have more political power than you think. 

Jon looks like Ned, not only in his appearance but also in his personality - both are honorable and both are leaders of Winterfell. In the books, Catelyn is also upset to see that Jon looks like Ned much more than her own sons. Jon might be Rhaegar’s son, but he was raised as the son of Ned Stark. He is a Stark, just as Ned reminds us in the trailer. He is the living embodiment of his father’s values.

This parallel is not a mere coincidence. Everything was thought of. Jon and Sansa are clearly compared to Ned and Catelyn - who did not only loved each other, but managed to work together as a powerful, united team. Sansa and Jon complete each other and help each other in a way no other characters in the series do. And yet, some dare say that Jonsa is not a thing…

(Also, although some people seem to consider D*nerys as the hero, she is not the focus of the trailer of the most important season of them all. She is not here at all. She is not even mentioned or alluded to. So much for being the hero. The Starks are the heroes, my friends. The Starks.)

(Although I do wonder where Bran is. But here again, he’s not Bran Stark anymore…)

Just like her mother, Sansa is a lady, a strong woman although she doesn’t fight with weapons. Both fight to protect their family. Both are the quiet, discrete ones who have more political power than you think. 

Jon looks like Ned, not only in his appearance but also in his personality - both are honorable and both are leaders of Winterfell. In the books, Catelyn is also upset to see that Jon looks like Ned much more than her own sons. Jon might be Rhaegar’s son, but he was raised as the son of Ned Stark. He is a Stark, just as Ned reminds us in the trailer. He is the living embodiment of his father’s values.

This parallel is not a mere coincidence. Everything was thought of. Jon and Sansa are clearly compared to Ned and Catelyn - who did not only loved each other, but managed to work together as a powerful, united team. Sansa and Jon complete each other and help each other in a way no other characters in the series do. And yet, some dare say that Jonsa is not a thing…

(Also, although some people seem to consider D*nerys as the hero, she is not the focus of the trailer of the most important season of them all. She is not here at all. She is not even mentioned or alluded to. So much for being the hero. The Starks are the heroes, my friends. The Starks.)

(Although I do wonder where Bran is. But here again, he’s not Bran Stark anymore…)

summary: I can’t be the only one thinking that the teaser is actually how Bran will show Jon, Sansa and Arya what the future holds and...
body:
I can’t be the only one thinking that the teaser is actually how Bran will show Jon, Sansa and Arya what the future holds and why they need to be together…Right?

First thing I thought when I saw it, the three walking separately and then meeting, was that Bran was actually using his powers to make their minds travel. This is also why he is not there. This is why the damn fire extinguished and the feather froze - this is how Bran sees things happening and wants to show them with all the effects needed to make them understand.

Of course the voice overs are a bit too much. And of course this might all be wishful thinking.

But I wouldn’t put it aside like that. Specially if he does this AFTER telling them who Jon really is.

summary: Fun Fact: Jon and Sansa were standing so close to each other 99% of us thought they were about to hold hands. There was a...
body: Fun Fact: Jon and Sansa were standing so close to each other 99% of us thought they were about to hold hands. There was a significant amount of space between Sansa and Arya. None of this was done by accident! With the extra Ned and Cat parallels, the show 1000% want us to group Jon and Sansa as a couple in our minds. All of this promo has been hella strategic to prepare our minds for season 8!
